00:51:00,373 --> 00:51:02,125
-Hey, you!
-Fight outside!

773
00:51:02,209 --> 00:51:04,252
-Get out!
-Get out!

774
00:51:04,336 --> 00:51:05,629
Let go of me!

775
00:52:15,991 --> 00:52:18,493
Mi-joo. Seon-gyeom. You're here.

776
00:52:19,911 --> 00:52:20,787
Hey.

777
00:52:21,371 --> 00:52:23,665
-Have you been well?
-As always.

778
00:52:23,748 --> 00:52:26,543
-Let me go.
-You let go first.

779
00:52:26,626 --> 00:52:27,752
Goh Ye-chan!

780
00:52:28,461 --> 00:52:29,838
-Mom?
-Ms. Dong.

781
00:52:29,921 --> 00:52:31,256
Hello, ma'am.

782
00:52:31,339 --> 00:52:33,216
-Who is she?
-She's her mom.

783
00:52:33,800 --> 00:52:35,051
What? Boxing?

784
00:52:35,135 --> 00:52:37,304
Seriously, boxing?

785
00:52:38,638 --> 00:52:40,890
-Were you aware of this?
-No, ma'am.

786
00:52:40,974 --> 00:52:42,767
-Were you in on it too?
-No, ma'am.

787
00:52:44,227 --> 00:52:46,771
Mr. Jeong, don't tell me you knew as well.

788
00:52:46,855 --> 00:52:48,273
Well…

789
00:52:53,862 --> 00:52:55,113
What's going on?

790
00:52:55,697 --> 00:52:56,823
Is this a gathering?

791
00:52:56,906 --> 00:52:59,034
-Ms. Seo!
-Dan-ah!

792
00:52:59,117 --> 00:53:01,578
-What's going on?
-Let me explain.

793
00:53:10,378 --> 00:53:11,671
Hey, Mi-joo!

794
00:53:37,697 --> 00:53:40,492
You, brat. Let's talk at home. Follow me.

795
00:53:40,575 --> 00:53:42,494
-Wait.
-Ms. Seo, I'm taking a half-day.

796
00:53:42,577 --> 00:53:43,703
-Let me go.
-Follow me!

797
00:53:43,787 --> 00:53:47,957
-Ye-jun, don't forget my bag!
-Is this the only cafe in Seoul?

798
00:53:48,917 --> 00:53:51,336
Why are you causing a scene at my cafe?

799
00:53:51,419 --> 00:53:52,670
Why?

800
00:54:19,823 --> 00:54:21,116
What happened to your hand?

801
00:54:22,617 --> 00:54:24,953
I'm going to get it checked out today.

802
00:54:25,036 --> 00:54:26,287
I think it's due to work.

803
00:54:28,581 --> 00:54:30,542
The fireworks I bought were too big.

804
00:54:30,625 --> 00:54:32,168
There's so much to clean up.

805
00:54:33,503 --> 00:54:35,046
Why are you here?

806
00:54:35,130 --> 00:54:36,714
I was invited.

807
00:54:37,549 --> 00:54:39,634
And I owe Ms. Seo so…

808
00:54:41,678 --> 00:54:44,431
Would you have still come
if you knew I'd be here?

809
00:55:18,673 --> 00:55:21,676
Damn it. I told you not to do it.

810
00:55:21,759 --> 00:55:23,094
This is all because of you.

811
00:55:23,178 --> 00:55:24,637
Both of you, quiet.

812
00:55:26,931 --> 00:55:27,974
I wasn't loud.

813
00:55:28,057 --> 00:55:29,726
You have a loud voice to begin with.

814
00:55:29,809 --> 00:55:31,644
I feel like an outcast.

815
00:55:32,228 --> 00:55:33,563
You guys are too harsh.

816
00:55:34,147 --> 00:55:36,065
Make sure you clean everything up.

817
00:55:36,149 --> 00:55:38,568
And stop causing a mess
at someone else's workplace.

818
00:55:46,117 --> 00:55:47,243
By the way,

819
00:55:47,827 --> 00:55:49,496
how are you two related?

820
00:55:49,579 --> 00:55:51,331
Your name wasn't on the family tree.

821
00:55:53,041 --> 00:55:54,459
I'm a bastard.

822
00:55:59,255 --> 00:56:00,423
A bastard?

823
00:56:03,009 --> 00:56:05,011
This is a secret,
so keep it on the down-low.

824
00:56:05,094 --> 00:56:06,221
What?

825
00:56:07,305 --> 00:56:08,681
Okay.

826
00:56:14,145 --> 00:56:15,230
And

827
00:56:16,356 --> 00:56:18,358
today isn't her birthday.

828
00:56:18,900 --> 00:56:21,277
It's fake. She wasn't born today.

829
00:56:22,278 --> 00:56:24,405
She was born before Myeong-min,

830
00:56:25,031 --> 00:56:28,409
but Dad only registered her birthday
after he was born.

831
00:56:29,994 --> 00:56:31,746
I really didn't want to tell you this,

832
00:56:31,829 --> 00:56:34,457
but I did so you wouldn't ruin
her day again.

833
00:56:44,592 --> 00:56:45,885
It won't take long.

834
00:56:45,969 --> 00:56:48,638
Goodness. When will you clean that up?

835
00:56:48,721 --> 00:56:50,849
-It's okay. You can go first.
-Okay.

836
00:57:21,337 --> 00:57:22,547
Hello?

837
00:57:25,216 --> 00:57:27,302
-Right now?
-Yes.

838
00:57:27,385 --> 00:57:29,929
I can't seem to reach Ms. Bang.

839
00:57:32,181 --> 00:57:34,309
She probably has bad reception.

840
00:57:38,187 --> 00:57:39,355
Okay.

841
00:57:44,152 --> 00:57:46,446
Why are you doing such a poor job?

842
00:57:46,529 --> 00:57:48,698
How are we to trust her with our kids?

843
00:57:48,781 --> 00:57:49,782
I'm truly sorry.

844
00:57:49,866 --> 00:57:50,867
What's going on?

845
00:57:50,950 --> 00:57:54,621
Sir, Su-bin got in a fight
with another student.

846
00:57:55,330 --> 00:57:58,833
-He's here instead of her--
-Are you educating them properly?

847
00:57:58,917 --> 00:58:00,585
Where are her parents?

848
00:58:00,668 --> 00:58:02,378
He's that athlete.

849
00:58:03,087 --> 00:58:04,297
Are you him?

850
00:58:04,380 --> 00:58:06,716
You were in charge of them
before the scandal.

851
00:58:06,799 --> 00:58:10,720
We've filed in our complaints.
I refuse to let you train my son.

852
00:58:11,387 --> 00:58:13,056
He has no right to train anyone.

853
00:58:13,139 --> 00:58:16,267
Forget it. Where's the coach?
I want to see her right now.

854
00:58:16,851 --> 00:58:20,396
I'm struggling to manage everything.

855
00:58:22,190 --> 00:58:26,361
I'm sorry.
It's all because I'm a lousy adviser.

856
00:58:26,444 --> 00:58:27,487
Don't say that.

857
00:58:28,613 --> 00:58:31,157
Is Su-bin in class?

858
00:58:31,908 --> 00:58:34,494
She's not here.

859
00:58:35,328 --> 00:58:37,246
She's been suspended starting today.

860
00:58:38,373 --> 00:58:41,084
The victim's mother demands
an apology from her parents.

861
00:58:41,167 --> 00:58:43,795
But Su-bin… You know her story.

862
00:58:43,878 --> 00:58:45,838
We shouldn't be apologetic

863
00:58:45,922 --> 00:58:47,882
after only hearing one side of the story.

864
00:58:49,676 --> 00:58:52,929
If she's still at fault
after hearing her side of the story,

865
00:58:53,012 --> 00:58:54,514
then I'll apologize to them.

866
00:59:40,852 --> 00:59:43,187
You shouldn't drink
while taking these antibiotics.

867
00:59:43,271 --> 00:59:46,315
Do you mean I can't drink for a week?
They gave me a week's worth.

868
00:59:46,399 --> 00:59:48,609
Don't forget to keep your hand
bandaged when showering.

869
00:59:49,360 --> 00:59:52,280
Are you sure I can't even have one sip?

870
00:59:52,363 --> 00:59:53,948
You know my answer.

871
01:00:08,504 --> 01:00:10,506
Hello. Here's the prescription.

872
01:00:10,590 --> 01:00:12,633
Okay. One minute.

873
01:00:12,717 --> 01:00:13,885
Okay.

874
01:00:16,596 --> 01:00:18,264
Mi-joo.

875
01:00:18,347 --> 01:00:21,184
-What?
-Hello.

876
01:00:21,267 --> 01:00:23,102
I can't believe I ran into you here.

877
01:00:26,022 --> 01:00:28,858
I love your fingernails.
Did you do them yourself?

878
01:00:28,941 --> 01:00:30,276
Yes, it's my hobby.

879
01:00:30,359 --> 01:00:33,905
Mi-joo, you can talk casually.

880
01:00:33,988 --> 01:00:35,698
-Should I?
-Yes.

881
01:00:36,491 --> 01:00:37,867
Did you go to that hospital?

882
01:00:37,950 --> 01:00:41,120
I have inflammation in my fingers.

883
01:00:42,371 --> 01:00:45,583
I fell down some stairs.

884
01:00:46,292 --> 01:00:49,128
I'm usually good at avoiding them

885
01:00:49,212 --> 01:00:50,838
but I couldn't that day.

886
01:00:52,090 --> 01:00:53,925
Are you being bullied at school?

887
01:00:57,595 --> 01:01:00,306
That student ridiculed me and said
I couldn't learn anything

888
01:01:00,389 --> 01:01:02,016
from someone who committed assault.

889
01:01:05,478 --> 01:01:06,813
Does Mr. Ki know about this?

890
01:01:10,274 --> 01:01:12,985
I don't think I can lie to his face,

891
01:01:13,069 --> 01:01:14,278
so I've been dodging him.

892
01:01:14,362 --> 01:01:16,405
I don't want to hurt him.

893
01:01:19,909 --> 01:01:23,704
They said the track and field team
could break up because of me.

894
01:01:25,873 --> 01:01:27,250
How is that your fault?

895
01:01:27,834 --> 01:01:28,709
Are you a big shot?

896
01:01:34,757 --> 01:01:36,634
I shouldn't be laughing,

897
01:01:37,426 --> 01:01:39,220
but that was hilarious.

898
01:01:39,303 --> 01:01:40,680
I tend to be funny.

899
01:01:46,060 --> 01:01:49,564
If I tell them the truth and reconcile,

900
01:01:50,773 --> 01:01:52,900
do you think everything
will turn out well?

901
01:01:55,153 --> 01:01:57,697
Should I tag along with you?
I have a lot of free time.

902
01:01:59,323 --> 01:02:00,908
This is my problem.

903
01:02:01,909 --> 01:02:03,870
If I run away…

904
01:02:05,246 --> 01:02:08,499
-No, if I do--
-Then let's have some tteokbokki.

905
01:02:09,208 --> 01:02:10,334
I know a tasty place.

906
01:02:10,418 --> 01:02:13,171
Ms. Oh Mi-joo, Ms. Lee Su-bin.
Your medication is ready.

907
01:02:13,254 --> 01:02:14,505
-Okay.
-Okay.

908
01:02:22,054 --> 01:02:23,181
Hello.

909
01:02:23,764 --> 01:02:25,474
I'm Lee Su-bin.

910
01:02:25,558 --> 01:02:27,101
I have something to tell you.

911
01:02:28,853 --> 01:02:29,937
So you're the girl.

912
01:02:30,021 --> 01:02:31,731
Bring your parents, not you.

913
01:02:31,814 --> 01:02:34,650
I live with my aunt.

914
01:02:34,734 --> 01:02:37,069
And she's very busy.

915
01:02:37,153 --> 01:02:38,738
I want to apologize.

916
01:02:39,405 --> 01:02:41,574
And I don't deserve to be suspended.

917
01:02:42,700 --> 01:02:44,410
You really are ignorant, aren't you?

918
01:02:44,493 --> 01:02:47,163
Chang-seop grabbed me first,
so I tried to stop him--

919
01:02:47,246 --> 01:02:50,499
Hey. How dare you blame my son?

920
01:02:51,083 --> 01:02:53,669
Bring your aunt then.
I have no business with you.

921
01:02:54,337 --> 01:02:56,964
This is the problem with ignorant kids.

922
01:03:03,971 --> 01:03:05,097
Hey! Who are you?

923
01:03:05,181 --> 01:03:06,641
Who are you? Are you crazy?

924
01:03:07,308 --> 01:03:08,559
A bit?

925
01:03:09,143 --> 01:03:10,353
Hey!

926
01:03:12,146 --> 01:03:14,440
Are you nuts?

927
01:03:14,523 --> 01:03:15,942
-I am.
-What?

928
01:03:16,025 --> 01:03:18,444
I'm totally nuts,
and I don't know what I'm capable of.

929
01:03:18,527 --> 01:03:20,905
Treat her like you just did again
if you're curious to find out.

930
01:03:20,988 --> 01:03:22,365
Then I'll really throw this.

931
01:03:23,157 --> 01:03:25,493
Who are you to meddle in our affair?

932
01:03:25,576 --> 01:03:27,203
Me? I'm her sister.

933
01:03:29,872 --> 01:03:32,416
What's the big deal about having parents?

934
01:03:33,793 --> 01:03:35,211
Let's go eat some tteokbokki.

935
01:03:36,170 --> 01:03:37,380
Su-bin!

936
01:03:39,507 --> 01:03:41,259
Did you cry? She did this, didn't she?

937
01:03:41,342 --> 01:03:42,718
-Let me go!
-Hey!

938
01:03:42,802 --> 01:03:44,804
Why are you doing this?

939
01:03:44,887 --> 01:03:46,347
Did you make her cry?

940
01:03:46,430 --> 01:03:47,640
So?

941
01:03:47,723 --> 01:03:50,142
Why do you want to join track and field?

942
01:03:50,226 --> 01:03:51,477
Why would you?

943
01:03:51,978 --> 01:03:53,771
You bad-mouthed Mr. Ki.

944
01:03:53,854 --> 01:03:55,439
Let me go!

945
01:03:56,732 --> 01:03:58,567
I did that out of jealousy

946
01:03:59,193 --> 01:04:00,736
since you liked him so much.

947
01:04:02,029 --> 01:04:04,448
Why would you be jealous?

948
01:04:04,532 --> 01:04:06,033
Because I like you!

949
01:04:07,159 --> 01:04:08,369
That's why.

950
01:04:10,663 --> 01:04:11,664
What?

951
01:04:12,290 --> 01:04:14,542
You idiot! You fool!

952
01:04:14,625 --> 01:04:17,670
I told you to study.
Now you want to join the track team?

953
01:04:18,254 --> 01:04:21,090
Don't be cruel to her.
I'm going to protect her.

954
01:04:21,173 --> 01:04:24,093
Who are you to protect her? Come here.

955
01:04:24,176 --> 01:04:26,846
Goodness, kids these days
are so passionate.

956
01:04:26,929 --> 01:04:29,265
-Su-bin!
-Stop calling her name!

957
01:04:29,348 --> 01:04:30,558
Let's go.

958
01:04:32,768 --> 01:04:34,312
What do you think about him?

959
01:04:34,395 --> 01:04:36,188
-Well…
-That hurts.

960
01:04:38,649 --> 01:04:39,525
Su-bin.

961
01:04:40,109 --> 01:04:42,194
What took you so long? Did you eat?

962
01:04:42,945 --> 01:04:44,447
-Hello.
-Hello.

963
01:04:44,530 --> 01:04:46,365
Who is she?

964
01:04:46,449 --> 01:04:48,701
She's a friend. I like her.

965
01:04:49,285 --> 01:04:50,953
-I see.
-Hello.

966
01:04:51,037 --> 01:04:53,372
I wanted to buy her dinner.

967
01:04:53,456 --> 01:04:54,623
Were you waiting?

968
01:04:54,707 --> 01:04:56,125
It's okay.

969
01:04:56,208 --> 01:04:58,669
Your track and field teacher came today
as well.

970
01:04:58,753 --> 01:05:00,338
He waited for a long time.

971
01:05:00,963 --> 01:05:02,882
I think he's left.

972
01:05:02,965 --> 01:05:06,427
I guess he came again. It's cold today.

973
01:05:07,553 --> 01:05:10,264
You can talk to him later.
It's a happy ending after all.

974
01:05:10,973 --> 01:05:12,266
Thank you for today.

975
01:05:12,350 --> 01:05:14,560
-Don't mention it. Go.
-Goodbye.

976
01:05:14,643 --> 01:05:16,520
-Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

977
01:05:16,604 --> 01:05:17,605
Let's go.

978
01:05:18,731 --> 01:05:19,940
Are you okay?

979
01:06:14,787 --> 01:06:16,956
-Seon-gyeom--
-Don't go.

980
01:06:20,709 --> 01:06:22,586
I won't, so let go of this.

981
01:06:22,670 --> 01:06:24,004
I know you will.

982
01:06:30,761 --> 01:06:32,221
Let me go, and we'll talk.

983
01:06:32,304 --> 01:06:34,849
Wait. Let's just stay like this
for a minute.

984
01:06:36,851 --> 01:06:37,935
I've…

985
01:06:40,646 --> 01:06:42,523
never been stubborn about anything.

986
01:06:44,859 --> 01:06:47,236
So I don't know how to do it.

987
01:06:51,031 --> 01:06:52,658
But could you not teach me?

988
01:06:54,368 --> 01:06:55,619
Not teach you what?

989
01:07:00,541 --> 01:07:01,876
How to break up.

990
01:07:08,591 --> 01:07:10,968
You can teach me everything else,

991
01:07:15,890 --> 01:07:18,225
but could you not teach me that?

992
01:07:24,982 --> 01:07:26,150
Can you just…

993
01:07:30,696 --> 01:07:32,531
like me?

994
01:07:40,122 --> 01:07:41,373
Please.

995
01:07:46,003 --> 01:07:48,088
Please, Ms. Oh.

996
01:08:21,664 --> 01:08:23,415
Catch me if you can.

997
01:08:25,167 --> 01:08:26,585
Do I still look like a kid to you?

998
01:08:26,669 --> 01:08:28,796
Yes, and that's exactly why

999
01:08:28,879 --> 01:08:30,589
I should keep you close at all times.

1000
01:08:31,215 --> 01:08:32,925
You didn't come home last night.

1001
01:08:33,008 --> 01:08:34,593
-Yes.
-Are you not coming home again?

1002
01:08:35,177 --> 01:08:38,013
I'm so frustrated that I can't sleep.

1003
01:08:38,097 --> 01:08:41,058
It wouldn't be that hard
to figure out where he is.

1004
01:08:41,141 --> 01:08:42,268
What about you?

1005
01:08:42,351 --> 01:08:44,311
-How dare you run away?
-What? Me?

1006
01:08:44,937 --> 01:08:48,148
I knew she was crazy,
but not to this extent.

1007
01:08:48,232 --> 01:08:49,316
Where should I sleep tonight?

1008
01:08:51,485 --> 01:08:52,361
I'll pounce on you.

1009
01:08:52,444 --> 01:08:56,448
-I miss you.
-Why don't you join our agency?

1010
01:08:56,532 --> 01:08:57,783
I'd like us to work together.

1011
01:08:57,866 --> 01:08:59,243
You did a good job.

1012
01:08:59,326 --> 01:09:02,121
Then why don't you come over
for some ramyeon?

1013
01:09:02,997 --> 01:09:04,790
We'll have the house to ourselves.

1014
01:09:06,166 --> 01:09:11,171
Subtitle translation by: Ja-won Lee
